	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with Celt. Nothing wrong with your 2-hs practice sword. It is a nice weapon but a bit slow being it's only draw back. For 2-hs you can begin looking for a Deepwater Harpoon. 1 less point of damage but a 40 delay which is considerably faster and it is Paladin only with a nice Wisdom and Stamina bonus. During the course of the battle you will do more damage with the Harpoon than you will with the bigger-hitting Practice Sword although less per hit. But no Thistle Shield. They sell for about 400 plat and it will serve you well into your 30's unless you are one of those players that has a LOT of extra cash and can just go buy you a Xalgoz or something like that.<br><br>As for 1-hs, you DEFINITELY need to keep that skill up. I know this from experience because I didn't do it! Then at level 29 I got Ghoulbane and my 1-hs skill was awful!&nbsp;&nbsp;I worked very hard to get it up and finally have it maxed. Fortunately, from level 22-30 and then 30-39 there is not a lot of skills to put your practice points into so I dumped 30 practice points into 1-hs and made a big leap. It still took me a LONG time to get it up to its current 165 max, so learn from my mistake and practice it now.  Once you hit 30 you will use a 1-hs/shield combo MUCH more often than you did pre-30.<br><br>Get in a group that isn't completely dependent on your damage output, get a fast/quick 1-hs weapon and get after it. You can still contribute to the damage in the group but the rapid attacks will help your skill increase. <br><br>As for a guild, I disagree a little with Celt. You don't have to have a guild. One would "perhaps" be helpful in obtaining Ghoulbane and perhaps with a few quests, but you can do it without a guild too. It is not necessary by any means and a decision you should not take lightly. Choose wisely or don't choose at all. <br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>32nd Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
